source: Allow access to the Keycloak SSO form.
Drupal's user login and registration pages will redirect to Keycloak. Existing users will be able to login using their Drupal credentials at /keycloak/login.
Enable role mapping via the Keycloak user client role mapping
Enables Open Social OpenID Connect Keycloak sign on and user data synchronization.
Name of the user role claim token. This can be a fully qualified name like "additional.roles". In this case, the user roles will be taken from the nested "roles" attribute of the "additional" claim.
Provides a pluggable client implementation for the OpenID Connect protocol.
The base URL of your Keycloak server. Typically https://example.com[:PORT]/auth.
This label will be displayed on user login page.
